race.comment: UNDERRATED (2) raced handy and boxed on strongly but found a couple better last start over this distance at Rockhampton. Down in class today and draws a beautiful gate so he looks a big chance to add to his already impressive record. DALT JAZ (6) doesn't win often but continues to race in great heart. Tried hard but just came up short last time out in a similar race here. Yet to miss the placings in six at this venue and should build on that record today. WHATTA WHITT (10) mixes his form. Just missed two back then blew the start which put paid to his chances here at this distance most recently. Draws the fence and is a winning hope if he puts his mind to it. DEFERENTIAL (1) has changed stables and comes here off an eight-week break. Will find this far easier than the latest assignments. Market watch recommended. Last start Cairns winner OUR IMPACT (4) is lightly raced and capable of another forward showing.
